\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Frank doesn't recommend \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 freezing poultry. However, if a bird must be held beyond three days, freezing will keep it wholesome.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 How do I freeze poultry?
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 When freezing is necessary, seal chicken or other poultry in an airtight container, heavy plastic bag, plastic wrap, foil or fre\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ezer paper.  
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Try to have the wrapping tight against the chicken because any place where it isn't, small ice crystals will form. That means moisture has been drawn from the meat, and where that's happened, the meat will be tough and breading won't stick. 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Frozen uncooked chicken can be stored up to six months; frozen cooked chicken should be used within three months. (Personally I try to avoid freezing chicken \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
since I know that freezing makes the chicken less tender and less juicy. Still, in spite of good intentions, I sometimes end up doing it. I've learned to make it a point to have a wax marking pencil and freezer tape handy, so I can label the package with 
