 rather than microwaving them if tenderness is a top priority for you.  Microwaving is significantly faster, but there's a greater risk of toughness when you microwave breast meat.  Breast meat is fairly dry to begin with, and you don't have a whole lot o
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 f\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  latitude between overcooking and undercooking. With breast meat, there's a trade-off between the speed of microwaving and the reliability of frying or roasting.
